CommonFields.Title: Enhancement of the mechanical properties of poly(styrene-co-acrylonitrile) with poly(methyl methacrylate)-grafted multiwalled carbon nanotubes
Author: Wang, Mian
Pramoda, K.P.
Goh, Suat Hong
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemistry, National University of Singapore, 3 Science Drive 3, Singapore 117543, Singapore

Heating.Description: refluxing as-received MWNTs in concentrated nitric acid

ChooseParameter.Other: wash thoroughly with deionized water and dry tetrahydrofuran
wash with dry THF for several times

Mixing.Description: mix in a dry three-neck flask with a magnetic stirring bar

ChooseParameter.Other: The mixture was degassed three times.

Heating.Description: The mixture was 70 8C oil bath under nitrogen for 72 h.

ChooseParameter.Other: The THF solution was filtered through 0.2-mm PTFE membranes.
The THF solution was washed with dry THF for several times to completely remove monomer and non-grafted PMMA.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Equipment: TA Instruments DMA2980 dynamic mechanical analyzer
Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: heating rate: 3 degree Celsius per minute under nitrogen; Frequency: 1 Hz
The strain rate was 5 mm/min under a load of 1 kN at room temperature.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: heating rate: 10 degree Celsius per minute under nitrogen atmosphere
